# Frontend Patterns

## API Calls
All backend calls go through Next.js API proxy routes (`app/api/v1/**/route.ts`).
Client components call `/api/v1/...` (relative), proxy adds `BACKEND_URL` + `X-API-Key`.
Never call EC2 directly from client code.

## Settings Sync
When adding a pipeline setting:
1. Add to `PipelineSettings` interface in `lib/types.ts`
2. Add UI control in `app/settings/page.tsx`
3. The `onChange` callback calls the backend settings API

## Sidebar (job-history.tsx)
- Builds job counts from the `jobs[]` array, NOT from `project.job_count`
- Must fetch `?limit=100` to cover all projects (default limit is 30)

## Agent Relay (agent-status.tsx)
- `useAgentLoop` polls EC2 for tasks, forwards to companion, posts results back
- `POLL_INTERVAL_ACTIVE = 500ms`, `POLL_INTERVAL_IDLE = 10000ms`
- Health checks every 15s to companion localhost:9876

## Component Conventions
- `"use client"` at top of interactive components
- shadcn/ui components in `components/ui/`
- App-specific components in `components/`
- Use `cn()` from `lib/utils` for className merging
